<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900919-0141</DOCNO><DOCID>900919-0141.</DOCID><HL>   McGraw-Hill, Firm   In France to Launch   European Data Service</HL><DATE>09/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   MHP EUROP</CO><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><LP>   NEW YORK -- McGraw-Hill Inc.'s F.W. Dodge division andPublications du Moniteur, a subsidiary of CEP CommunicationsS.A., Paris, agreed to launch a service to supply informationon European construction.   The new Pan European Construction Service will providedetailed printed information on all major new constructionprojects in Europe that construction and building-productscompanies bid on, a spokesman for Dodge said. The servicewill link seven major European providers ofconstruction-project news.</LP><TEXT>   Start-up costs will be minimal, the spokesman said,because the two services must only reroute their current flowof information to subscribers in different countries. The newservice is expected to be available to an unspecified numberof subscribers by the fall of 1991. Subscribers will pay $500to $50,000 annually for the service, he said.   Through F.W. Dodge, McGraw-Hill is a major provider ofconstruction-project news in the U.S. Its Dodge Europedivision has similar activities in Europe.   Publications du Moniteur's weekly Le Moniteur is a leadingEuropean construction-project publication in France and Spainwith a circulation of 75,000, according to McGraw-Hill.</TEXT></DOC>